label.value: Mucinous Tubular and Spindle Cell Carcinoma of the Kidney

value.value: A low grade carcinoma of the kidney characterized by the presence of tubules which are separated by mucinous stroma. Often the tubular structures have a spindle cell appearance.  Patients are usually asymptomatic and occasionally they may present with hematuria or flank pain.
A renal papillary adenoma which is characterized by basophilic cells with scant amount of cytoplasm.

A diffuse or multifocal peripheral neuropathy caused by the effects of a distant neoplasm. It may be attributed, in part, to the immune response to neoplasm-elaborated proteins. The neuropathy may be sensory, motor, mixed or autonomic. It may be the initial presentation of an occult neoplasm. Detection and resection of the neoplasm may result in cure.
A renal papillary adenoma which is characterized by eosinophilic cells.

A benign, solitary, and partially cystic neoplasm arising from the kidney. It occurs in children and adults. Presenting symptoms include hematuria and polycythemia. It is characterized by the presence of epithelial nodules embedded in a stroma containing spindle cells.
A mutation in the SMARCB1 gene that either inhibits expression of the SMARCB1 protein or results in the translation of an inactive SMARCB1 protein.
A congenital mesoblastic nephroma characterized by the presence of interlacing fascicles of fibroblastic cells, low mitotic activity, and collagen formation.
A congenital mesoblastic nephroma characterized by increased cellularity, sheet-like proliferation of fibroblastic cells, and increased mitotic activity.  Necrotic changes are commonly present.

label.value: Invasive Bladder Urothelial Carcinoma with Squamous Differentiation

value.value: An invasive urothelial carcinoma of the bladder that exhibits squamous differentiation.

label.value: Invasive Bladder Urothelial Carcinoma with Glandular Differentiation

value.value: An invasive urothelial carcinoma of the bladder that exhibits glandular differentiation.

label.value: Invasive Bladder Urothelial Carcinoma with Trophoblastic Differentiation

value.value: An invasive bladder urothelial carcinoma characterized by the presence of trophoblastic differentiation.
Invasive bladder urothelial carcinoma characterized by a nested growth pattern.
An epithelium-lined cyst located in the iris.
Invasive bladder urothelial carcinoma characterized by microcysts formation.
Invasive bladder urothelial carcinoma with lymphoepithelioma-like features.

label.value: Infiltrating Bladder Urothelial Carcinoma, Lymphoma-Like Variant

value.value: Invasive bladder urothelial carcinoma characterized by the presence of malignant cells with plasmacytoid features.
An invasive urothelial carcinoma of the bladder that exhibits spindle cell sarcomatoid features.

label.value: Invasive Bladder Sarcomatoid Urothelial Carcinoma with Heterologous Elements

value.value: Invasive bladder sarcomatoid urothelial carcinoma characterized by the presence of heterologous elements.

label.value: Invasive Bladder Sarcomatoid Urothelial Carcinoma without Heterologous Elements

value.value: Invasive bladder sarcomatoid urothelial carcinoma characterized by the absence of heterologous elements.

label.value: Invasive Bladder Clear Cell (Glycogen-Rich) Urothelial Carcinoma

value.value: An invasive urothelial carcinoma of the bladder characterized by the presence of clear (glycogen-rich) cells.
Invasive bladder urothelial carcinoma characterized by the presence of lipid laden tumor cells.

label.value: Invasive Bladder Giant Cell Urothelial Carcinoma

value.value: An invasive urothelial carcinoma of the bladder with giant cells.
A non-invasive papillary neoplasm of the bladder urothelium.
A rare variant of well differentiated squamous cell carcinoma, usually associated with bladder schistosomiasis.
A verrucous squamous cell carcinoma of the bladder that is caused by Schistosoma hematobium.
A rare, benign neoplasm of bladder that is composed of papillary cores with overlying histologically benign squamous epithelium.
A rare adenocarcinoma that arises in the bladder. It is characterized by intestinal type glands and resembles colonic adenocarcinoma.
An adenocarcinoma, not otherwise specified, arising from the bladder.
A rare primary adenocarcinoma of the bladder. Histologically it is characterized by malignant cells floating in pools of mucin.
A rare variant of bladder adenocarcinoma. It is characterized by the presence of a mixture of polygonal hepatoid cells and glandular adenocarcinoma cells.
A variant of bladder adenocarcinoma that histologically consists of more than one growth pattern such as enteric, mucinous or signet ring types.
A rare variant of carcinoma of the urachal remnant of bladder.
A rare bladder adenocarcinoma that develops from the urachal remnant.
A urothelial carcinoma of the urinary bladder that arises from the urachal epithelium.
A rare variant of bladder urachal carcinoma with squamous cell features.

label.value: Intestinal Metaplasia of Bladder Urachal Epithelium

value.value: A rare morphologic variant of bladder carcinoma characterized by the presence of malignant glandular epithelial cells and clear cells forming a tubulo-cystic pattern.
A rare morphologic variant of bladder adenocarcinoma characterized by the presence of malignant glandular epithelial cells and clear cells forming a papillary pattern.
A rare morphologic variant of bladder adenocarcinoma characterized by the presence of malignant glandular epithelial cells and clear cells forming a diffuse pattern.
